# English Version (translation; the Chinese version prevails)

This Agreement licenses the "Software" in two separate parts — the **Source Code** and
the **Compiled Application** — under different terms. The "Software" means digitallife
（数字人生）developed by 许道斌 (Daobin Xu) (the "Author"), together with its source
code, binaries, documentation, icons, configuration, and related resources. **The
Software is PROPRIETARY and NOT open source.**

## Article 1. Source Code — Proprietary, All Rights Reserved

The Source Code of the Software is the exclusive property of the Author. Except for the
Author, no person or entity may, without prior **WRITTEN** authorization, use, copy,
download, store, modify, translate, adapt, decompile, disassemble, reverse-engineer, or
distribute, transfer, rent, lend, sell, sublicense, or publicly disseminate any part of
the Source Code.

**The fact that the Source Code may be viewable (source-visible) does NOT constitute any
license to use it; "visible" does not mean "usable."**

## Article 2. Compiled Application — Free for Non-Commercial Use

For the compiled application officially released by the Author through an **Official
Channel** in **UNMODIFIED** form (such as the officially signed and notarized DMG
installer, the "Official Application"), and subject to the restrictions in this Article,
the Author grants the following parties engaged in **Non-Commercial Use** a
non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use and run the Official Application **FREE
OF CHARGE**:

- individuals (for personal purposes such as study, research, experimentation, or hobby);
- non-profit organizations;
- educational and research institutions;
- government bodies.

**This license is limited to "use / run" only and does NOT include any of the following:**

- redistributing, reselling, renting, lending, publicly distributing, or sublicensing the
  Official Application — it must be obtained from an **Official Channel** and must **NOT**
  be forwarded, copied, or redistributed by others;
- modifying, decompiling, disassembling, or reverse-engineering the Official Application,
  or removing or circumventing its digital signature, copyright notices, or update mechanism;
- incorporating or embedding the Official Application or any part thereof into other
  products or services.

## Article 3. Commercial Use Requires Authorization

Any **Commercial Use** (as defined in Article 4) requires prior **WRITTEN** (commercial)
authorization from the Author.

## Article 4. Definitions

**"Non-Commercial Use"** means use not primarily intended for or directed toward
commercial advantage or monetary compensation. The following constitute Non-Commercial
Use: (a) use by a natural person for private, non-profit purposes such as study, research,
experimentation, or hobby; (b) use by non-profit organizations, educational and research
institutions, and government bodies within the scope of their non-profit or public functions.

**"Commercial Use"** means any use other than the Non-Commercial Use described above, and
requires prior written authorization. It includes, without limitation:

- **any use by a for-profit organization (including enterprises, companies, sole
  proprietorships, etc.) in the course of its business — even if the Software is not sold
  or redistributed, and even if used solely internally by its employees — which constitutes
  Commercial Use;**
- using the Software to provide paid products or services, or in activities that directly
  or indirectly generate revenue;
- using the Software in paid training, consulting, or outsourcing services.

**"Official Channel"** means the following location(s) controlled by the Author for
officially releasing the Official Application: the Releases page of the GitHub repository
`https://github.com/Link-X/digitallife-releases`, and any other release location later
designated **IN WRITING** by the Author (such as an official website or the App Store).
Copies obtained from any source other than the above are not within the scope of the
license granted herein.

